AGI -&nbsp; The predominant colour is red, with the slogans written in white: a graphic that closely resembles what characterizes the Pse, the European family of the Pd. Elly Schlein launches the campaign for Europeans from the headquarters of the Foreign Press in Rome and declines it through a series of dichotomies: "Clean air, not poisons"; "The sea, not a cemetery"; "A family, not a target." The starting point is, however, "Europe we want". That is, Schlein explains, "a more social Europe that leads to the necessary ecological transition."
&nbsp;
"The dexter", explains the leader dem, "are still in a phase of transition of climate emergency. Think about the most frequent extreme events in our country. We must accompany families and enterprises in the necessary changes, otherwise there will be no propaganda that it holds. It is this government which has decided to remove the incentives for young farmers. We hold together a social question and a climate issue, we will make our proposals independently when we have to correct the shooting on some decisions taken. Faced with today's challenges, from the ecological transition to the contrast of inequalities, we need not deny the European space, as the right ones do, but to fill in the space of democracy, overcoming the system of unanimity".
&nbsp;
Another focus of the Pd campaign is health: "We think there is no room for propaganda on the health issue. Since the government is the right of Meloni, health spending has steadily declined and is returning to pre-pandemia levels. It is expected a year and a half to make a gastroscopy, two years to make a mammography. The right hand definances public health, does not unlock the turn over and emptys the departments", recalls the secretariat that continues: "Clean air, not poisons: to this should serve the investments of the Pnrr and the Green Deal. Emissions hurt the environment but also hurt the health of citizens."
&nbsp;
And again: "The sea, not a cemetery: We have succeeded in bringing the idea of a European Nostrum Sea into the programme of socialists. We must avoid drowning people. I want to add that we continue to fight for European solidarity on migration policies. It means opening access routes to all European countries. We need to build a legal alternative to human trafficking. We will continue to insist on a real overcoming of the Dublin Regulation. We voted against the European immigration pact because it is dangerous for asylum seekers and individual countries. Who enters Italy for us enters Europe and is not true solidarity pay twenty thousand euros for each person who chooses not to welcome. It is a pact that provides for a series of measures such as child restraint with the obligation to take biometric data from six years. We are against this securitary drift." For this reason Schlein reiterates: "The Pd will no longer accept any support for the Libyan Coast Guard."
&nbsp;
The right chapter also includes the 'family' item. "A family, not a target: for us there are many types of families and they all deserve respect and recognition of rights, especially when we talk about girls and children. We will continue to be at the side of the children of homogeneous families. Europe cannot go on this ground. I found significant and important last week's vote in the European Parliament: abortion is a fundamental right still too little recognized in this country. We must guarantee in every structure a share of non-objective doctors." The close topicality finally leads the Pd to say: "A Europe for peace, not war: the debate of these months shows that it is not an obvious phrase. We have been insisting on this position for many months and continue to insist. It is a dynamic that mainly concerns the consequences on civilian victims of these wars. As European federalists, we are fighting for the common defence. There is no common defence by creating an empty box within the European commission, with a commissioner without powers and without portfolio."

